00:24:10,950 --> 00:24:12,494
- Looks good.
- What?

503
00:24:12,518 --> 00:24:13,917
It's perfect.

504
00:24:13,953 --> 00:24:15,914
Let's start weaning
her off bypass.

505
00:24:15,938 --> 00:24:17,905
She's undergone

506
00:24:17,940 --> 00:24:19,506
two major surgeries at once.

507
00:24:21,777 --> 00:24:25,595
Her heart was already
weak to begin with.

508
00:24:25,630 --> 00:24:28,081
It may never restart.

509
00:24:28,117 --> 00:24:30,650
Even if it does restart,
she may never wake up.

510
00:24:30,685 --> 00:24:31,969
Please clear.

511
00:24:40,028 --> 00:24:41,461
Sinus rhythm.

512
00:24:44,132 --> 00:24:46,217
Look at that.

513
00:24:47,970 --> 00:24:49,453
That's a win for now.

514
00:24:49,488 --> 00:24:52,439
I'm going to give you a
pass on how you behaved

515
00:24:52,474 --> 00:24:53,986
because I know
how upset you are.

516
00:24:54,010 --> 00:24:57,661
But I certainly won't forget.

517
00:24:58,681 --> 00:24:59,813
It's all you.

518
00:25:13,712 --> 00:25:15,362
Conrad.

519
00:25:15,397 --> 00:25:17,514
Dr. Moore, how we doing?

520
00:25:17,550 --> 00:25:19,349
Your organ is perfect.

521
00:25:19,384 --> 00:25:21,585
The timing is
practically a miracle.

522
00:25:28,927 --> 00:25:30,394
Hey.

523
00:25:30,429 --> 00:25:33,063
- We have a liver.
<i>- Incredible.</i>

524
00:25:33,098 --> 00:25:36,333
Tyler is still down here.
They had no beds in the ICU.

525
00:25:36,369 --> 00:25:39,036
All right, we'll send him
up to the OR now. Let's go.

526
00:25:55,704 --> 00:25:58,589
Take good care of her.

527
00:26:10,503 --> 00:26:12,485
How is she?

528
00:26:14,590 --> 00:26:18,291
Uh... alive.

529
00:26:18,326 --> 00:26:20,560
We fixed the valve.

530
00:26:20,595 --> 00:26:24,998
Her heart's beating,
but beyond that?

531
00:26:27,069 --> 00:26:30,420
I don't know if I'm gonna
be okay if she's not.

532
00:26:30,456 --> 00:26:33,107
You want to see the baby?

533
00:27:02,321 --> 00:27:04,321
♪ ♪

534
00:27:42,645 --> 00:27:45,628
Hey. How's it going?

535
00:27:45,664 --> 00:27:47,864
So far so good.

536
00:27:51,820 --> 00:27:53,815
Three more hours
and you're official.

537
00:27:56,075 --> 00:27:58,474
That first day you told
me, "Go be a doctor

538
00:27:58,510 --> 00:28:00,577
or go be something else."

539
00:28:00,612 --> 00:28:02,562
Yeah, I remember.

540
00:28:02,598 --> 00:28:04,693
And you said this is
the best job in the world,

541
00:28:04,717 --> 00:28:06,099
despite everything.

542
00:28:07,168 --> 00:28:09,653
Because of everything.

543
00:28:09,688 --> 00:28:13,557
That day I watched
a young girl die.

544
00:28:13,592 --> 00:28:17,177
And today I watch good
doctors save a young man's life.

545
00:28:17,212 --> 00:28:19,897
And right now all
I am thinking is...

546
00:28:23,469 --> 00:28:26,786
what a privilege it
is to be a part of it.

547
00:29:01,590 --> 00:29:03,222
Dr. Cain still in surgery?

548
00:29:03,275 --> 00:29:06,259
Uh, I don't know.
He was in OR Two.

549
00:29:17,989 --> 00:29:19,973
Where is Dr. Cain?

550
00:29:20,009 --> 00:29:22,058
Uh, he left 15 minutes ago.

551
00:29:22,093 --> 00:29:23,388
Who are you?

552
00:29:23,412 --> 00:29:25,145
I'm his resident.

553
00:29:28,434 --> 00:29:30,267
- Uh...
- What's going on?

554
00:29:31,520 --> 00:29:34,237
- Page Dr. Cain.
- What is going on? Talk to<i> me.</i>

555
00:29:34,272 --> 00:29:36,133
I lost control of the bypass,
can't stop the bleeding.

556
00:29:36,157 --> 00:29:38,308
He's losing
perfusion to his brain.

557
00:29:38,344 --> 00:29:39,821
Page any attending.
I need help now.

558
00:29:39,845 --> 00:29:41,978
Hang on, I'm coming in!

559
00:29:42,013 --> 00:29:45,176
- What's happening?
- I can't finish the patch. The artery's shredding.

560
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:47,195
Take a deep breath.
I'm not kidding.

561
00:29:47,219 --> 00:29:50,236
Take a deep breath. Do what
I say and this will be all right.

562
00:29:50,272 --> 00:29:51,989
There's blood everywhere.

563
00:29:52,024 --> 00:29:53,818
I've only done
this in-in a sim lab.

564
00:29:53,842 --> 00:29:55,820
First we need to
see the field. Suction.

565
00:29:55,844 --> 00:29:58,261
Now I'm gonna help you get
proximal and distal control.

566
00:29:58,297 --> 00:30:00,175
- All right.
- Grab the vessel clamps
and put them

567
00:30:00,199 --> 00:30:01,809
- where my fingers are.
- All right.

568
00:30:01,833 --> 00:30:03,311
- Do you see that?
- Yeah, right there.

569
00:30:03,335 --> 00:30:05,769
Okay, good. Now what?

570
00:30:05,804 --> 00:30:07,254
Um, reinforce the patch.

571
00:30:07,289 --> 00:30:08,956
Uh-huh. Do it.

572
00:30:15,330 --> 00:30:17,330
Bajwa here. Dr. Cain
left the hospital.

573
00:30:18,801 --> 00:30:20,817
He did what?

574
00:30:24,907 --> 00:30:26,735
It's gonna have to
wait. I got an urgent text.

575
00:30:26,759 --> 00:30:30,126
Yeah, don't worry,
it's been handled.

576
00:30:30,162 --> 00:30:32,563
- By whom?
- Yeah... by me and Dr. Bajwa,

577
00:30:32,598 --> 00:30:33,796
who happened to be on deck.

578
00:30:33,832 --> 00:30:35,076
I've been a surgeon a long time.

579
00:30:35,100 --> 00:30:36,628
I've seen attendings
come in drunk,

580
00:30:36,652 --> 00:30:38,663
I've seen 'em fall asleep
from sheer exhaustion.

581
00:30:38,687 --> 00:30:39,831
I've seen incompetence
and heroics and everything

582
00:30:39,855 --> 00:30:42,739
in between, but this
defies description.

583
00:30:42,774 --> 00:30:47,310
Your patient nearly died, you
left him wide open on the table.

584
00:30:47,346 --> 00:30:50,413
You want an attaboy
for saving one life?

585
00:30:50,449 --> 00:30:52,649
I save dozens every day,
hundreds by the week.

586
00:30:52,685 --> 00:30:55,347
- Get over it.
- Do you save them
or manage not to kill them?

587
00:30:55,371 --> 00:30:58,638
Wheeling a patient with
a blown brain into the ICU

588
00:30:58,673 --> 00:31:00,985
and hooking them up to a vent
is not a life-saving procedure.

589
00:31:01,009 --> 00:31:02,671
- It's abusive.
- Oh.

590
00:31:02,695 --> 00:31:04,311
Look who's talking.

591
00:31:04,346 --> 00:31:06,157
One glass of ten-year-old
bourbon and your residents

592
00:31:06,181 --> 00:31:10,016
cannot wait to share the
tales of the mighty HODAD.

593
00:31:10,052 --> 00:31:11,384
Hands of Death and Destruction.

594
00:31:11,419 --> 00:31:12,697
That is what they
call you, isn't it?

595
00:31:12,721 --> 00:31:14,732
Patients dead after a
routine appendectomy,

596
00:31:14,756 --> 00:31:16,723
catching fire in the OR?

597
00:31:16,759 --> 00:31:18,992
Yeah, I've made
mistakes, but I was there.

598
00:31:19,027 --> 00:31:22,011
With my staff in the
OR, not off joyriding

599
00:31:22,047 --> 00:31:23,875
while my patients
were left incapacitated.

600
00:31:23,899 --> 00:31:26,066
I have saved the lives
of kings and princesses

601
00:31:26,101 --> 00:31:27,517
from every corner of this world.

602
00:31:27,553 --> 00:31:29,019
They worship me.

603
00:31:29,054 --> 00:31:31,704
They want to name
their children after me.

604
00:31:31,740 --> 00:31:33,540
They will never forget who I am.

605
00:31:33,575 --> 00:31:35,370
- But it seems that you have.
- No.

606
00:31:35,394 --> 00:31:36,904
You're the one who's
forgotten who I am:

607
00:31:36,928 --> 00:31:39,195
chief of surgery and your boss.

608
00:31:39,231 --> 00:31:41,498
You will answer to the board.

609
00:31:49,558 --> 00:31:51,741
Yeah? What do you think?

610
00:31:51,777 --> 00:31:54,377
Wow. Nic let you out
of the house like that?

611
00:31:56,665 --> 00:31:58,326
What are you doing?

612
00:31:58,350 --> 00:32:00,044
I've gotten a free sandwich
here ever since I started.

613
00:32:00,068 --> 00:32:02,903
- These guys love me.
- Is that right?

614
00:32:02,938 --> 00:32:06,389
Let me guess, fried egg.

615
00:32:06,425 --> 00:32:09,392
Yeah. How'd you know that?

616
00:32:09,428 --> 00:32:10,471
They like you,

617
00:32:10,495 --> 00:32:12,140
but they don't
like you that much.

618
00:32:12,164 --> 00:32:15,214
Have you been buying
my lunch this whole time?

619
00:32:15,250 --> 00:32:17,767
Yeah. Something my resident
did for me. It's a tradition.

620
00:32:17,803 --> 00:32:20,437
You just pay it forward,
do the same for your intern.

621
00:32:20,472 --> 00:32:23,306
It's a way to say thank you

622
00:32:23,342 --> 00:32:26,292
for all the hard
work they put in.

623
00:32:26,328 --> 00:32:29,662
Last one. Better enjoy it.

624
00:32:38,373 --> 00:32:40,273
Listen.

625
00:32:42,461 --> 00:32:43,860
I want you to know that...

626
00:32:43,896 --> 00:32:46,646
I do know.

627
00:32:49,902 --> 00:32:51,822
Hey, I want to
show you something.

628
00:32:58,309 --> 00:33:01,344
- You mean...
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

629
00:33:02,580 --> 00:33:05,315
Wow.

630
00:33:05,351 --> 00:33:07,217
- Congratulations.
- Aah!

631
00:33:07,252 --> 00:33:09,686
I haven't... asked her yet.

632
00:33:09,722 --> 00:33:11,482
I just have to find
the right moment.

633
00:33:11,506 --> 00:33:13,167
- She needs to say yes.
- Oh, she will.

634
00:33:13,191 --> 00:33:15,358
You guys are inevitable.

635
00:33:17,028 --> 00:33:18,611
No, I know how I feel about Nic.

636
00:33:18,647 --> 00:33:21,498
That's never changed.
It never will change.

637
00:33:23,151 --> 00:33:25,685
She's everything.

638
00:33:27,673 --> 00:33:30,123
- Hi.
- Hi.

639
00:33:30,158 --> 00:33:31,857
Oh, no, no.

640
00:33:31,910 --> 00:33:33,660
Come on.

641
00:33:34,729 --> 00:33:37,547
How's Mina?

642
00:33:37,582 --> 00:33:39,365
Rumpled and grumpy.

643
00:33:39,400 --> 00:33:42,969
She slept in a chair by
Adaku's side last night.

644
00:33:43,004 --> 00:33:45,188
And Adaku?

645
00:33:45,223 --> 00:33:48,141
Critical.

646
00:33:48,176 --> 00:33:49,993
She's intubated and sedated.

647
00:33:50,028 --> 00:33:51,344
It's gonna be a long road ahead.

648
00:33:51,379 --> 00:33:53,158
She'll be in the
hospital for a while.

649
00:33:53,182 --> 00:33:55,098
The baby, on the other hand,

650
00:33:55,133 --> 00:33:57,650
might be able to
go home in a week.

651
00:33:57,686 --> 00:33:59,903
With Mina.

652
00:34:01,256 --> 00:34:03,356
Wow, that's a scary thought.

653
00:34:03,409 --> 00:34:06,743
Ho...

654
00:34:23,895 --> 00:34:28,582
I'm sorry... for earlier.

655
00:34:28,617 --> 00:34:30,750
The things I said.

656
00:34:34,272 --> 00:34:35,855
But I was not wrong.

657
00:34:35,891 --> 00:34:37,434
If we had taken her
to surgery first thing...

658
00:34:37,458 --> 00:34:39,409
Mina, stop.

659
00:34:42,731 --> 00:34:46,299
Taking care of her was my job.

660
00:34:48,736 --> 00:34:51,887
Look, I get it.

661
00:34:51,923 --> 00:34:54,674
It's been a rough 24
hours for everybody.

662
00:34:56,795 --> 00:34:59,746
And you have another
challenge ahead of you now.

663
00:35:04,936 --> 00:35:06,369
She's just so small.

664
00:35:16,932 --> 00:35:18,914
The surgery went perfectly.

665
00:35:18,950 --> 00:35:21,284
We're hopeful
for a full recovery.

666
00:35:21,319 --> 00:35:23,152
That's wonderful.

667
00:35:25,440 --> 00:35:28,274
How you feeling?

668
00:35:28,327 --> 00:35:32,478
I've been better,
but I can't complain.

669
00:35:32,514 --> 00:35:35,248
Still here, right?

670
00:35:35,283 --> 00:35:37,316
I know I have you
to thank for that.

671
00:35:37,351 --> 00:35:40,520
Well, the person we
have to thank is the donor.

672
00:35:42,473 --> 00:35:45,124
He gave you a
very precious gift.

673
00:35:45,160 --> 00:35:48,477
Look, I promise I
learned my lesson.

674
00:35:49,981 --> 00:35:52,481
I'm not gonna make
that mistake again, okay?

675
00:35:54,653 --> 00:35:58,388
I'd like to be sure of that.

676
00:35:58,423 --> 00:36:01,308
I want you to start by
being honest with your mom.

677
00:36:04,829 --> 00:36:06,657
- I can't do that.
- No, no, no, no.

678
00:36:06,681 --> 00:36:09,615
It's okay. It's important.
She needs to know.

679
00:36:09,650 --> 00:36:14,554
And this is why... I want
you to get counseling.

680
00:36:14,589 --> 00:36:16,351
You need to talk to
someone about why you tried

681
00:36:16,375 --> 00:36:18,775
to take your own life to make
sure it doesn't happen again.

682
00:36:31,523 --> 00:36:33,683
Are you sure the transplant
surgeon heard you?

683
00:36:33,708 --> 00:36:35,392
Positive.

684
00:36:35,427 --> 00:36:36,704
- What did he say?
- Nothing.

685
00:36:36,728 --> 00:36:38,339
He walked away
without speaking to me.

686
00:36:38,363 --> 00:36:40,529
Okay, this is bad.

687
00:36:40,565 --> 00:36:42,064
Well, maybe, maybe not.

688
00:36:42,100 --> 00:36:43,494
We don't know if
he'll tell anyone.

689
00:36:43,518 --> 00:36:44,829
The surgery's done,
the outcome is good.

690
00:36:44,853 --> 00:36:46,319
They can't turn back the clock.

691
00:36:46,355 --> 00:36:47,999
This shouldn't even be an issue.

692
00:36:48,023 --> 00:36:49,851
There are no
guidelines from UNOS

693
00:36:49,875 --> 00:36:51,241
telling transplant centers

694
00:36:51,276 --> 00:36:53,504
whether to give organs to
someone who attempted suicide.

695
00:36:53,528 --> 00:36:56,413
Transplant protocol varies
from hospital to hospital.

696
00:36:56,448 --> 00:36:59,182
If Tyler had gone
to Atlanta General,

697
00:36:59,217 --> 00:37:01,517
they would have approved
the transplant surgery

698
00:37:01,552 --> 00:37:03,631
with virtually no
questions asked, but...

699
00:37:03,655 --> 00:37:07,407
Chastain doesn't work that way.

700
00:37:07,442 --> 00:37:10,426
So what do we do now?

701
00:37:11,913 --> 00:37:14,280
Behave as if nothing happened.

702
00:37:30,065 --> 00:37:33,633
Where's the board? I
requested a meeting.

703
00:37:33,668 --> 00:37:35,251
Your request was denied.

704
00:37:35,287 --> 00:37:36,702
Well, you can't do that.

705
00:37:36,737 --> 00:37:38,071
It's in the hospital charter.

706
00:37:38,106 --> 00:37:40,389
The chief of surgery
may request...

707
00:37:40,424 --> 00:37:42,925
You've been stripped
of that title, Dr. Bell.

708
00:37:45,130 --> 00:37:46,579
What'd you say?

709
00:37:46,615 --> 00:37:50,933
Dr. Cain is Chastain's
new chief of surgery.

710
00:37:50,969 --> 00:37:55,287
All future requests
will go through him.

711
00:38:05,700 --> 00:38:07,633
♪ ♪

712
00:38:12,440 --> 00:38:14,607
Randolph, I heard.

713
00:38:14,642 --> 00:38:16,525
Are you all right?

714
00:38:16,561 --> 00:38:18,611
Tending to my first love.

715
00:38:18,646 --> 00:38:20,491
Putting my affections
where they stand a chance

716
00:38:20,515 --> 00:38:22,265
of being returned.

717
00:38:22,300 --> 00:38:25,084
Will you leave Chastain?

718
00:38:25,120 --> 00:38:27,720
I won't give 'em
the satisfaction.

719
00:38:30,058 --> 00:38:33,509
And if they fire me, they will
owe me a substantial sum.

720
00:38:33,545 --> 00:38:36,129
But they will fire me.

721
00:38:36,164 --> 00:38:39,282
You know how the pressure
drops before a storm,

722
00:38:39,317 --> 00:38:41,684
and you're not aware of
it in any conscious way,

723
00:38:41,720 --> 00:38:44,354
but you know
something is changing?

724
00:38:44,389 --> 00:38:46,200
I finalized your
paperwork last night.

725
00:38:46,224 --> 00:38:50,310
You have a five-year
contract, ironclad.

726
00:38:52,547 --> 00:38:54,397
I don't know what to say.

727
00:38:56,351 --> 00:38:58,818
Just be what you
are, a great surgeon.

728
00:39:07,012 --> 00:39:09,140
All right, everybody, can I
have your attention, please?

729
00:39:09,164 --> 00:39:11,680
Let's welcome our
new chief resident,

730
00:39:11,716 --> 00:39:13,366
Dr. Conrad Hawkins.

731
00:39:18,339 --> 00:39:19,422
Speech!

732
00:39:19,457 --> 00:39:21,507
Oh, yeah.

733
00:39:21,543 --> 00:39:23,371
If Devon wants a speech,
he's gonna get a speech.

734
00:39:23,395 --> 00:39:24,511
Keys to the palace.

735
00:39:24,546 --> 00:39:27,397
Got your own office, a
call room with a shower.

736
00:39:27,432 --> 00:39:29,110
- Ooh.
- She's all yours.

737
00:39:29,134 --> 00:39:31,028
Thank you, thank you.
We'll see if you're all

738
00:39:31,052 --> 00:39:32,563
still clapping for me when
I'm busting your asses

739
00:39:32,587 --> 00:39:33,753
first thing in the morning.

740
00:39:35,574 --> 00:39:37,991
- Did you meet your interns yet?
- No.

741
00:39:38,026 --> 00:39:39,086
I don't know anything about 'em.

742
00:39:39,110 --> 00:39:40,737
- Nice coat, Hawkins.
- Thank you.

743
00:39:40,761 --> 00:39:42,840
Not that it matters much.
I was never chief resident.

744
00:39:42,864 --> 00:39:45,782
Look at me now.

745
00:39:45,817 --> 00:39:48,351
So, I hear

746
00:39:48,386 --> 00:39:51,053
your office has a
brand-new 72-inch flat-screen

747
00:39:51,089 --> 00:39:52,054
and an Xbox.

748
00:39:52,090 --> 00:39:53,100
You got time for<i> Call of Duty?</i>

749
00:39:53,124 --> 00:39:54,751
- Oh, yeah, let's make it happen.
- All right.

750
00:39:54,775 --> 00:39:57,760
- Just the man I was looking for!
- Aah!

751
00:39:57,795 --> 00:39:59,345
I can use the new shower, right?

752
00:39:59,380 --> 00:40:02,015
Anytime, anytime.

753
00:40:02,050 --> 00:40:03,183
Hey, how about me?

754
00:40:03,218 --> 00:40:04,883
Ah, not a chance.

755
00:40:04,936 --> 00:40:06,080
What, the free fried
egg sandwiches

756
00:40:06,104 --> 00:40:09,388
- weren't enough for you?
- Mm...

757
00:40:10,909 --> 00:40:12,524
This is impressive.

758
00:40:12,560 --> 00:40:14,480
I've never had my
name on a door.

759
00:40:14,962 --> 00:40:17,579
Let me try.

760
00:40:19,284 --> 00:40:21,284
Maybe they haven't
programmed it yet.

761
00:40:22,788 --> 00:40:24,737
Dr. Hawkins.

762
00:40:24,772 --> 00:40:26,872
Uh, I'll-I'll take
that. Thank you.

763
00:40:26,908 --> 00:40:30,727
You lied to the, the
transplant board.

764
00:40:30,762 --> 00:40:32,556
We don't give organs to
patients who are suicidal.

765
00:40:32,580 --> 00:40:35,247
Wait, Tyler's not suicidal.
It was a stupid mistake.

766
00:40:37,085 --> 00:40:39,786
Am I talking to you?

767
00:40:42,523 --> 00:40:44,724
You're fired.

768
00:40:46,644 --> 00:40:49,429
Ah, that rule's arbitrary
and you know it.

769
00:40:49,464 --> 00:40:51,075
You don't care
about Tyler Warzel,

770
00:40:51,099 --> 00:40:53,783
you care that I'm
a whistleblower.

771
00:40:53,818 --> 00:40:56,419
That's what this is about.

772
00:40:56,454 --> 00:40:59,138
Huh? I blew the whistle

773
00:40:59,173 --> 00:41:02,158
on a bad drug, and you're
afraid for your bottom line.

774
00:41:03,828 --> 00:41:05,995
You're afraid of me.

775
00:41:07,782 --> 00:41:09,632
And you should be.

776
00:41:11,652 --> 00:41:14,787
Security will escort you out.

777
00:41:14,822 --> 00:41:17,373
Give me your pager.

778
00:41:21,863 --> 00:41:23,963
Thank you.

779
00:41:38,596 --> 00:41:40,830
- What's going on?
- They're firing Conrad.

780
00:41:43,267 --> 00:41:44,628
- You can't do this.
- Whoa, whoa.

781
00:41:44,652 --> 00:41:46,647
- Get your hands off me.
- Hey, hey, hey, hey!

782
00:41:46,671 --> 00:41:47,681
It's okay, it's okay.

783
00:41:47,705 --> 00:41:49,305
Then I'll quit, too.

784
00:41:49,340 --> 00:41:50,857
No, you'll stay here.

785
00:41:52,660 --> 00:41:55,044
I'll see you tonight.

